 for bestpractices and # Raw Payload Browser & Audit Export

## Overview
You are building an Admin-focused feature set named Raw Payload Browser & Audit Export within a larger platform. This tool enables administrators to:
- Browse and filter raw ingestion payloads
- Inspect provenance details and related metadata
- Replay ingestion for specific payloads (idempotent replays)
- Build and export signed audit artifacts for selected NarrativeEvents
- Support admin operations like DLQ handling, user-support actions, and system health monitoring
- Serve as a hub connected to an Admin Dashboard and Admin Operations & Monitoring pages

This feature must be designed for reliability, auditability, and security, with strong runtime safety guarantees (null/undefined guards, safe array handling, and robust API validation). It should integrate cleanly with the existing design system, UI patterns, and necessary authentication/authorization layers.

---

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Raw Payload Browser & Audit Export page is an Admin tool that allows security-conscious administrators to locate, review, and manage raw ingestion payloads from ingestion pipelines. It provides provenance inspection, safe replay capabilities, and a signed-audit artifact builder to export artifacts for a curated set of NarrativeEvents.

Goals:
- Empower admins to browse raw ingestion payloads with precise filtering (source, date range, company/ticker, ingestion batch id)
- Provide a comprehensive payload viewer showing full raw JSON/text, provenance metadata, integrity hash, and download options
- Enable idempotent ingestion replay on a per-payload basis or on a selected set
- Offer an Export Artifact Builder to generate signed JSON artifacts and a human-readable PDF export for selected NarrativeEvents
- Provide admin-controlled retention commands (mark for retention or purge)
- Ensure all operations are logged and auditable, with proper role-based access control
- Integrate with Admin Operations & Monitoring for replay orchestration, DLQ handling, and system health status
- Link to Admin Dashboard for quick access to user management and export artifacts

UI/UX expectations:
- A central, predictable layout that supports deep drill-down into a payload while keeping context for provenance
- Clear indicators of payload status (ingested, failed, retried, etc.)
- A robust payload viewer with copy/download options and integrity checks
- An Export Builder UI that supports selecting multiple NarrativeEvents, configuring signing, and producing export artifacts (signed JSON + PDF)
- Admin-only retention controls with explicit warnings and safeties to prevent accidental purge
- Consistent with the design system in typography, color, spacing, and components

API integrations:
- The page relies on backend services for: payload search, payload details, provenance data, replay orchestration, signed artifact generation, retention controls, and export PDF generation. No external APIs are assumed; the APIs live within the project’s backend.

Connected Pages:
- Admin Dashboard
- Admin Operations & Monitoring

Connected Features:
- Admin Operations & Monitoring (replay, DLQ, support actions, health monitoring)

Mandatory runtime safety and coding standards must be applied to all code generated for this task (see “Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety” below).

---

## Components to Build
- PayloadSearchFilters
  - Props: onChangeFilters, initialFilters
  - Features: source dropdown, date range picker, ticker/company selector, ingestion batch id input, quick presets
  - Safety: guards against null/undefined values; always treat data sources as possibly null and coerce to arrays

- PayloadList
  - Props: payloads (array), total, onPageChange, onSelectPayloads
  - Data: columns showing id, timestamp, source, ticker, status, batchId
  - Safety: use (payloads ?? []).map(...) guard; ensure pagination handles empty results gracefully

- PayloadViewerPanel
  - Props: payload, onClose, onReplay, onExport
  - UI: shows raw JSON/text of payload, provenance metadata, integrity hash, download button
  - Safety: verify payload is an object; guard JSON rendering; provide a read-only code block with safe escaping

- ProvenancePanel
  - Props: provenanceData
  - UI: display provenance chain, related events, and replay feasibility notes
  - Safety: Array.isArray(provenanceData?.events) ? provenanceData.events.map(...) : []

- ReplayControl
  - Props: onReplayPayload, onReplaySelected
  - Behavior: idempotent replay, confirmation dialog, status feedback
  - Safety: confirm before replay; ensure IDs are strings; guard against missing payload

- ExportArtifactBuilder
  - Props: selectedNarrativeEvents (array), onGenerateExport
  - UI: multi-select summary, signing method selector, artifact type (JSON/PDF), progress/status
  - Safety: validate selections; ensure export generation handles empty/invalid selections gracefully

- RetentionControls
  - Props: payloadsSelected (array), onMarkRetention, onPurge
  - UI: toggle retention flag, purge confirmation; admin-only feature gating
  - Safety: confirm destructive actions; batch-safe operations

- AdminDashboardLinkCard
  - Props: sections/metrics data
  - UI: quick access to user management, audit exports, system health
  - Safety: resilient to missing data; use defaults

- SystemHealthPanel (shared with Admin Dashboard)
  - Props: healthMetrics
  - UI: show ingestion throughput, error rates, queue depths, replay success rate
  - Safety: guard against non-array metrics; default to empty object

- DataTablePagination
  - Reusable pagination component with pageSize, currentPage, totalItems
  - Safety: guard against null/undefined in totals

---

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks/Lund: React (TypeScript) with a router for page-level navigation
- State management: React useState/useReducer for local page state; consider context or a lightweight store for cross-page state if needed
- Accessibility: Ensure keyboard navigability, ARIA attributes for panels, and high-contrast focus outlines
- UI components: Build using the project’s design system (cards, grids, buttons, inputs, select, modal dialogs, badges)
- Data handling safety:
  - All arrays accessed via (items ?? []) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
  - Initialize all array state hooks with []: useState<Type[]>([])
  - Safely access API response shapes with destructuring defaults: const { items = [], total = 0 } = response ?? {}
  - Optional chaining everywhere: obj?.prop?.nested
- Networking:
  - Use fetch or the project’s HTTP client; wrap responses with safe guards
  - Validate response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
  - Debounce search/filter inputs if live search is supported
- Data persistence and caching:
  - Local cache for last used filters; ensure cache invalidation on logouts or significant data changes
- Security and RBAC:
  - Ensure UI elements that perform critical actions (replay, purge, export) are guarded by user roles
  - Hide or disable admin-only actions for unauthorized users
- Canvas/Visualization:
  - If you render charts (optional), keep visuals minimal (single-tone lines, light grids)
  - Provide tooltips for payload items with minimal raw snippet (safe escaping)

### Backend
- Endpoints (to be used by frontend):
  - GET /admin/payloads?filters... -> Paginated payloads
  - GET /admin/payloads/{id} -> Payload detail with provenance
  - POST /admin/payloads/{id}/replay -> Trigger ingestion replay (idempotent)
  - POST /admin/payloads/replay -> Replay for a batch or selected payloads
  - POST /admin/audit/export -> Generate signed audit artifact for selected NarrativeEvents
  - GET /admin/audit/export/{exportId}.pdf|json -> Retrieve export artifacts
  - PATCH /admin/payloads/{id}/retention -> Mark for retention
  - DELETE /admin/payloads/{id} -> Purge artifact (admin-only)
- Database tables/entities:
  - RawPayloads: id, source, ticker, batchId, timestamp, status, payloadJson (TEXT), hash, provenanceId, retentionFlag, retryCount
  - Provenance: id, payloadId FK, events JSON, provenanceChain, createdAt
  - NarrativeEvents: id, payloadId, eventId, eventData, signedJson, createdAt
  - AuditExports: id, userId, payloadSelectionId, exportType, status, createdAt, signedArtifactJson, pdfBlob
  - AdminActionsLog: id, userId, actionType, targetId, payloadDelta, timestamp
- Validation:
  - Validate all inputs server-side; reject invalid filters or missing authentication
  - For export generation, ensure integrity by signing with HMAC or PKI per project policy
- Reliability:
  - Idempotent replay endpoints, retry logic, and proper error codes
- Security:
  - RBAC checks on all admin endpoints
  - Encrypt sensitive data at rest if required
  - Audit logging for critical actions

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - User applies filters -> Frontend requests /admin/payloads with filters -> Backend returns payload list
  - User selects a payload -> Frontend fetches /admin/payloads/{id} for detail including provenance
  - User triggers replay -> Frontend calls /admin/payloads/{id}/replay or /admin/payloads/replay
  - User selects NarrativeEvents -> Frontend calls /admin/audit/export with selection -> Backend generates signed artifacts and stores in AuditExports
  - User uses RetentionControls -> Frontend calls retention endpoints
- Error handling:
  - Centralized error boundary and user-friendly error messages
  - Graceful handling of empty datasets or partial failures
- UX continuity:
  - Use consistent card surfaces, hover states, and micro-interactions across components
  - Maintain a clear back-and-forth flow between search, details, replay, and export

---

## User Experience Flow
- Step 1: Admin lands on Raw Payload Browser & Audit Export page
  - Page loads with a default date range (e.g., last 7 days) and empty results if no data
  - Filters panel at the top: Source, Date Range, Ticker/Company, Ingestion Batch ID
- Step 2: Admin applies filters
  - PayloadList updates with paginated results
  - Status highlights (ingested, failed) are visually distinct
- Step 3: Admin selects a payload
  - PayloadViewerPanel opens or side panel reveals full raw payload JSON/text
  - ProvenancePanel shows the provenance chain and relevant events
  - Integrity hash is displayed; Download button available
- Step 4: Admin replays payload
  - ReplayControl prompts for confirmation
  - On confirm, backend processes idempotent replay; status updates in UI
- Step 5: Admin builds audit export
  - Admin selects NarrativeEvents from the payload or a curated list
  - Open ExportArtifactBuilder: choose signing method, artifact type (JSON/PDF), and generate export
  - Backend signs and returns artifact; link to download PDF/JSON introduced
- Step 6: Retention controls
  - Admin marks selected payloads for retention or purge with confirmation dialogs
- Step 7: Admin Dashboard integration
  - Quick navigation to Admin Dashboard for system health metrics and user management
- Step 8: Audit and logs
  - All actions are logged; admin can view AuditExports, action logs, and export artifacts

---

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: Schema Highlights
- RawPayloads
  - id: string (PK)
  - source: string
  - ticker: string
  - batchId: string
  - timestamp: string (ISO 8601)
  - status: string (e.g., ingested, failed, retried)
  - payloadJson: string (TEXT)
  - hash: string
  - provenanceId: string (FK -> Provenance)
  - retentionFlag: boolean
  - retryCount: number
- Provenance
  - id: string (PK)
  - payloadId: string (FK -> RawPayloads)
  - events: array<NarrativeEventProvenance> stored as JSON
  - provenanceChain: string (description)
  - createdAt: timestamp
- NarrativeEvents (association to RawPayloads and provenance)
  - id: string (PK)
  - payloadId: string (FK -> RawPayloads)
  - eventId: string
  - eventData: JSON
  - signedJson: JSON
  - createdAt: timestamp
- AuditExports
  - id: string (PK)
  - userId: string
  - payloadSelectionId: string (reference to selection)
  - exportType: string (JSON|PDF)
  - status: string
  - createdAt: timestamp
  - signedArtifactJson: JSON
  - pdfBlob: binary/blob reference
- AdminActionsLog
  - id: string (PK)
  - userId: string
  - actionType: string
  - targetId: string
  - payloadDelta: JSON
  - timestamp: timestamp

API Endpoints (Routes and Methods)
- GET /admin/payloads
  - Query: filters (source, ticker, dateFrom, dateTo, batchId, status, page, pageSize)
  - Response: { data: RawPayload[], total: number }
- GET /admin/payloads/{id}
  - Response: { payload: RawPayload, provenance: Provenance, narrativeEvents: NarrativeEvent[] }
- POST /admin/payloads/{id}/replay
  - Body: { reason?: string }
  - Response: { success: boolean, jobId?: string, message?: string }
- POST /admin/payloads/replay
  - Body: { payloadIds: string[] } or { batchId?: string, filters?: object }
  - Response: { success: boolean, jobId?: string, scheduledCount?: number }
- POST /admin/audit/export
  - Body: { narrativeEventIds: string[], signingMethod: string, exportFormat?: string } 
  - Response: { exportId: string, status: string, downloadUrls: { json?: string, pdf?: string } }
- GET /admin/audit/export/{exportId}
  - Response: { signedArtifactJson, pdfBlobUrl, status }
- PATCH /admin/payloads/{id}/retention
  - Body: { retain: boolean }
  - Response: { success: boolean }
- DELETE /admin/payloads/{id}
  - Response: { success: boolean }

Security: Authentication & Authorization
- All admin endpoints require authenticated admin role
- RBAC ensures only authorized users can replay, purge, or export artifacts
- Tokens/Session must be validated; implement CSRF protection for destructive actions
- Audit trail captured for all critical admin actions

Validation
- On all API inputs, validate types and required fields
- Use robust defaults on the client:
  - data ?? [] for arrays
  - Array.isArray(payloads) ? payloads.map(...) : []
- Validate payload shapes with runtime checks on responses
- Ensure date ranges are valid, pageSize within allowed bounds, and strings are sanitized

Error Handling
- Centralized error handling with user-friendly messages
- Distinguish between client-side validation errors and server-side failures
- Provide retry guidance for transient errors where applicable

Performance
- Implement pagination on payload listings; avoid loading all payloads
- Debounce filters where applicable to reduce server load
- Keep payload detail fetches lean; load provenance and narrative events on demand

Testing
- Unit tests for frontend components guarding against null/undefined
- Integration tests for key flows: filter → select payload → replay → export
- End-to-end tests for admin actions (replay, retention, export)

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Raw Payload Browser page renders with fully functional filters (source, date range, ticker, batchId) and a paginated PayloadList.
- [ ] PayloadViewerPanel shows the full raw payload, provenance data, integrity hash, and a working download button; all arrays are guarded with proper null checks.
- [ ] Replay actions are idempotent, require admin confirmation, and report status in the UI; replay endpoints guard against missing payloads.
- [ ] Export Artifact Builder can select NarrativeEvents, sign artifacts, generate JSON and PDF exports, and provide download links; all data is validated server-side.
- [ ] Retention and purge controls are clearly labeled, gated to admin roles, and require explicit confirmation to execute.
- [ ] All API responses validate shapes at runtime; UI uses data ?? [] and Array.isArray() guards; useState([]) defaults for arrays.
- [ ] Admin Dashboard and Admin Operations & Monitoring integrations function in tandem with this page (replay status, system health, and quick access to user management).
- [ ] UI adheres to the given visual style, color palette, typography, spacing, and component behavior; accessibility requirements are met.

---

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system precisely. Adhere to:
- Card styles: white surfaces, light borders, soft shadows, 10–12px corner radii, hover lift
- Top navigation: brand mark left, navigation links centered/left, auth actions right; active states with subtle underline and accent dot
- Data visualization: minimal, single-tone lines, light grids, tooltips
- Controls: pill CTAs, minimal borders, focus outlines in #93C5FD
- Micro-interactions: 150–220ms for hover, 300ms for panel transitions
- Accessibility: high-contrast typography for primary text, keyboard focus indicators, screen-reader-friendly elements

Color Palette (as provided)
- Primary background: #FBFBFC
- Map/overlay: #F3F4F6
- Primary text: #111827
- Meta text: #6B7280
- Borders: #E5E7EB
- Card: #FFFFFF
- Accent badges: #FF6B4A
- Primary CTAs: #0F172A
- Focus: #93C5FD
- Positive indicator: #10B981

Typography and Layout
- Font: Inter / system-ui
- H1: 48–56px, bold
- H2: 24–32px
- Body: 16px
- Metadata: 12–14px
- Grid: 12-column with generous vertical rhythm
- Padding: 20–28px card padding; 12–16px controls padding
- Hierarchy: strong numerals, muted captions

Design Philosophy
- Modern, trustworthy, auditable
- Clarity, drill-down, enterprise polish
- Transparent provenance cues
- Fast scannability and predictable flows

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety
- Supabase-like pattern: use data ?? [] for arrays
- Always guard array methods: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays
- API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: obj?.prop?.nested
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

