  - retryCount: number
- Provenance
  - id: string (PK)
  - payloadId: string (FK -> RawPayloads)
  - events: array<NarrativeEventProvenance> stored as JSON
  - provenanceChain: string (description)
  - createdAt: timestamp
- NarrativeEvents (association to RawPayloads and provenance)
  - id: string (PK)
  - payloadId: string (FK -> RawPayloads)
  - eventId: string
  - eventData: JSON
  - signedJson: JSON
  - createdAt: timestamp
- AuditExports
  - id: string (PK)
  - userId: string
  - payloadSelectionId: string (reference to selection)
  - exportType: string (JSON|PDF)
  - status: string
  - createdAt: timestamp
  - signedArtifactJson: JSON
  - pdfBlob: binary/blob reference
- AdminActionsLog
  - id: string (PK)
  - userId: string
  - actionType: string
  - targetId: string
  - payloadDelta: JSON
  - timestamp: timestamp

API Endpoints (Routes and Methods)
- GET /admin/payloads
  - Query: filters (source, ticker, dateFrom, dateTo, batchId, status, page, pageSize)
  - Response: { data: RawPayload[], total: number }
- GET /admin/payloads/{id}
  - Response: { payload: RawPayload, provenance: Provenance, narrativeEvents: NarrativeEvent[] }
- POST /admin/payloads/{id}/replay
  - Body: { reason?: string }
  - Response: { success: boolean, jobId?: string, message?: string }
- POST /admin/payloads/replay
  - Body: { payloadIds: string[] } or { batchId?: string, filters?: object }
  - Response: { success: boolean, jobId?: string, scheduledCount?: number }
- POST /admin/audit/export
  - Body: { narrativeEventIds: string[], signingMethod: string, exportFormat?: string } 
  - Response: { exportId: string, status: string, downloadUrls: { json?: string, pdf?: string } }
- GET /admin/audit/export/{exportId}
  - Response: { signedArtifactJson, pdfBlobUrl, status }
- PATCH /admin/payloads/{id}/retention
  - Body: { retain: boolean }
  - Response: { success: boolean }
- DELETE /admin/payloads/{id}
  - Response: { success: boolean }

Security: Authentication & Authorization
- All admin endpoints require authenticated admin role
- RBAC ensures only authorized users can replay, purge, or export artifacts
- Tokens/Session must be validated; implement CSRF protection for destructive actions
- Audit trail captured for all critical admin actions

Validation
- On all API inputs, validate types and required fields
- Use robust defaults on the client:
  - data ?? [] for arrays
  - Array.isArray(payloads) ? payloads.map(...) : []
- Validate payload shapes with runtime checks on responses
- Ensure date ranges are valid, pageSize within allowed bounds, and strings are sanitized

Error Handling
- Centralized error handling with user-friendly messages
- Distinguish between client-side validation errors and server-side failures
- Provide retry guidance for transient errors where applicable

Performance
- Implement pagination on payload listings; avoid loading all payloads
- Debounce filters where applicable to reduce server load
- Keep payload detail fetches lean; load provenance and narrative events on demand

Testing
- Unit tests for frontend components guarding against null/undefined
- Integration tests for key flows: filter → select payload → replay → export
- End-to-end tests for admin actions (replay, retention, export)

---

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] The Raw Payload Browser page renders with fully functional filters (source, date range, ticker, batchId) and a paginated PayloadList.
- [ ] PayloadViewerPanel shows the full raw payload, provenance data, integrity hash, and a working download button; all arrays are guarded with proper null checks.
- [ ] Replay actions are idempotent, require admin confirmation, and report status in the UI; replay endpoints guard against missing payloads.
- [ ] Export Artifact Builder can select NarrativeEvents, sign artifacts, generate JSON and PDF exports, and provide download links; all data is validated server-side.
- [ ] Retention and purge controls are clearly labeled, gated to admin roles, and require explicit confirmation to execute.
- [ ] All API responses validate shapes at runtime; UI uses data ?? [] and Array.isArray() guards; useState([]) defaults for arrays.
- [ ] Admin Dashboard and Admin Operations & Monitoring integrations function in tandem with this page (replay status, system health, and quick access to user management).
- [ ] UI adheres to the given visual style, color palette, typography, spacing, and component behavior; accessibility requirements are met.

---

## UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project’s design system precisely. Adhere to:
- Card styles: white surfaces, light borders, soft shadows, 10–12px corner radii, hover lift
- Top navigation: brand mark left, navigation links centered/left, auth actions right; active states with subtle underline and accent dot
- Data visualization: minimal, single-tone lines, light grids, tooltips
- Controls: pill CTAs, minimal borders, focus outlines in #93C5FD
- Micro-interactions: 150–220ms for hover, 300ms for panel transitions
- Accessibility: high-contrast typography for primary text, keyboard focus indicators, screen-reader-friendly elements

Color Palette (as provided)
- Primary background: #FBFBFC
- Map/overlay: #F3F4F6
- Primary text: #111827
- Meta text: #6B7280
- Borders: #E5E7EB
- Card: #FFFFFF
- Accent badges: #FF6B4A
- Primary CTAs: #0F172A
- Focus: #93C5FD
- Positive indicator: #10B981

Typography and Layout
- Font: Inter / system-ui
- H1: 48–56px, bold
- H2: 24–32px
- Body: 16px
- Metadata: 12–14px
- Grid: 12-column with generous vertical rhythm
- Padding: 20–28px card padding; 12–16px controls padding
- Hierarchy: strong numerals, muted captions

Design Philosophy
- Modern, trustworthy, auditable
- Clarity, drill-down, enterprise polish
- Transparent provenance cues
- Fast scannability and predictable flows

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety
- Supabase-like pattern: use data ?? [] for arrays
- Always guard array methods: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays
- API response shapes: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: obj?.prop?.nested
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

